Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Library Technician - Night Circulation Prince George , BC Description The incumbent orients patrons to library services primarily during afternoon and evening hours at the Circulation Desk, including when a supervisor is not available to provide immediate support. The work involves maintaining user accounts and assisting with materials borrowing, finding and retrieving information, computer and technology services, and meeting room reservations. The person must exhibit good judgment, be prepared to make decisions independently, and model a collegial, team-based approach to work.Skills &amp; Qualifications:Recognized two (2 ) year diploma in Library and Information Technology, or equivalent (min. 2 years post-secondary).1 year or more relevant library/office/customer service experience. Previous library experience is required.Courses/training in Microsoft Office and library systems/databases.Computer experience required (e.g. library systems, word processing, database, spreadsheet, online applications), with keyboarding minimum 40 wpm, 90% accuracy.Ability to deal well with public and fellow employees.Ability to prioritize tasks, interpret library policies/procedures, work independently.Good organizational skills.Posting Number: 24-142SPFor full details and/or to apply, please visit our Career website https://cnc.peopleadmin.ca/postings/8835https://cnc.peopleadmin.ca/postings/8835. Compensation $57,423 per year Closes: 20 September, 2024 College of New Caledonia Prince George , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
