Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Administrative Services Coordinator North Vancouver , BC Description Administrative services coordinator (2024-12) North Vancouver City Library is seeking a motivated, conscientious, and upbeat Administrative Services Coordinator to join our team (regular full-time, 70 hours bi-weekly). Reporting to the Manager, People, Finance and IT, the administrative services coordinator is responsible to: Coordinate day-to-day administrative activities for the library, including planning, directing and reviewing the work of administrative services assistants; Coordinate and support recruitment, onboarding, training and development; and develop and maintain documents and systems for human resource administration;Schedule up to 60 employees and make daily adjustments to support operations in response to emergent staffing needs;Source and organize delivery of training based on identified organizational needs and priorities;Plan and implement programs and events that promote staff engagement and wellness; andSupport the implementation and evaluation of the library’s diversity, equity, access and inclusion priority actions. The successful candidate will bring:Strong supervisory skills and experienceA customer service mindsetA proactive, creative and collaborative approach to problem-solvingA commitment to employee development, engagement and wellnessA demonstrated commitment to advancing diversity, equity, accessibility and inclusionThe ability to balance priorities and work effectively in a dynamic environmentA toolkit for managing tasks and projects, and for completing a variety of work accurately, effectively and in a timely mannerIntermediate to advanced MS Office and Adobe Acrobat skillsStrong communication and conflict resolution skills If you thrive with a balance of routine and project-based work, if you enjoy streamlining workflows and solving problems collaboratively, and if you have a growth mindset and bring joy and good energy to the workplace – we are looking for you! Please see the attached Job Classification Specification (under review) for further details.Qualifications: Completion of a post-secondary diploma or degree in business or public administration, human resources or a related field, plus 3 to 5 years related experience in an office setting, or an equivalent combination of training and experience. Experience in a unionized, government and/or non-profit environment would be an asset. Apply to: Deb Hutchison Koep, Chief Librarian https://www.nvcl.ca/careers-library Note: When uploading documents to your profile, the maximum size allowed per document is 1MB. Please ensure the document file name and file extension is all lower case (i.e. .pdf and not .PDF). If you are having difficulty attaching documents, please click on the “question mark” icon on the top right side of the screen for technical support. Start date: Immediately Salary: $33.25 – $39.14/hour (pay grade 18; 2024 rates*) + benefits *Note: this classification is currently under review. Schedule: North Vancouver City Library offers a flexible work arrangement for full-time employees resulting in an additional rest day during each two-week period. Week 1 Monday – 8:30 a.m. – 4:45 p.m. Tuesday – 8:30 a.m. – 4:45 p.m. Wednesday – 8:30 a.m. – 4:45 p.m. Thursday – 8:30 a.m. – 4:45 p.m. Friday – 8:30 a.m. – 4:45 p.m. Week 2 Tuesday – 8:30 a.m. – 5 p.m. Wednesday – 8:30 a.m. – 4:45 p.m. Thursday – 8:30 a.m. – 4:45 p.m. Friday – 8:30 a.m. – 4:45 p.m. Schedules are reviewed periodically and subject to change. Evenings and weekends may be required. Closing date: September 15, 2024 at 5 p.m. North Vancouver City Library is committed to recruiting and hiring candidates that reflect the community we serve. We welcome applicants from diverse backgrounds, including Indigenous candidates, all identities, candidates who speak languages in addition to English, and persons with disabilities. Accommodations are available on request for candidates in all parts of the selection process. About us: North Vancouver City Library is located in the heart of the City of North Vancouver. As a valued public service, our library is a centre for discovery and dialogue, providing a gateway to lifelong learning and community connection through a balance of digital, traditional and emerging library services. Our decision-making is guided by deeply held values: https://www.nvcl.ca/about/missionClass No. TBD (currently under review)1. Nature and scope of workThis is multifaceted administrative, human resource and supervisory work involving responsibility for coordination and effective execution of administrative activities at the library. The role has responsibility for organization-wide scheduling and coordination of organizational development activities including training and DEI initiatives. In addition, they supervise a small group of administrative services assistants. Considerable independence of judgement and action is exercised in the performance of assigned duties. Unusual or complex problems or policy matters are discussed with the Manager, People, Finance and IT who reviews work periodically for accuracy and effectiveness.2. Illustrative Examples of WorkCoordinates day-to-day administrative activities for the library; develops, maintains, documents and communicates systems and processes to ensure efficient and effective delivery of administrative services; acts as a resource to library employees about day-to-day administrative questions.Oversees day-to-day financial functions including payroll, accounts payable and credit card reconciliation; reviews and verifies financial documents for accuracy; develops, maintains and updates tracking systems to ensure all financials are submitted in a timely manner.Assigns, reviews, plans, and supervises the day-to-day activities of administrative services assistants; provides on-going coaching, feedback and support; conducts annual goal-setting and performance reviews; addresses and corrects performance issues within scope; ensures administrative staff have skills, knowledge and resources required to support their work; acts as next level for concerns and complaints.Coordinates and supports job posting and hiring process, including drafting job postings, processing applications, liaising with applicants, and scheduling interviews (using applicant tracking software); prepares, tracks and completes on- and off-boarding of employees; ensures all necessary paperwork is completed; ensures employees are oriented and receive training according to their roles.Develops and maintains documents and systems for human resource administration, including tracking for seniority, increments, and benefits eligibility; drafts letters and enters information into 3rd party systems accordingly; processes and distributes appropriate forms.Schedules up to 60 employees in accordance with established practices, policies and procedures, and collective agreement; prepares and adjusts schedules in scheduling software; responds immediately to emergent staffing needs; liaises with supervisors regarding schedule changes; ensures appropriate documentation to process employee leave requests, such as vacation, leaves of absence, etc.Operationalizes the organization’s training and development strategy; sources and organizes suitable training programs; plans and coordinates programs and events to promote staff engagement and wellness; monitors training and conference budgets; develops and maintains system for tracking training and development activities; researches and makes recommendations for training and development to senior leadership.Fosters a positive and inclusive workplace culture by promoting diversity and inclusion activities; supports the implementation and evaluation of the library’s diversity, equity, access and inclusion framework and priority actions.Performs related work as required.3. Required Knowledge, Abilities and SkillsAbility to plan, assign, supervise and review the work of Administrative Services Assistants; mentor, support and inspire team members.Ability to identify, evaluate and coordinate training and development activities suitable for knowledge workers in a municipal environment.Ability to organize, prioritize and execute high-quality work in a dynamic and fast-paced environment.Ability to deal effectively with the public and co-workers; strong conflict resolution skills.Ability to communicate effectively, both verbally and in writing, and provide instruction to others.Ability to lead by example, identify issues and find effective solutions, and adapt to changing priorities.Considerable knowledge of office management and administration concepts, tools, processes and best practices.Considerable knowledge of human resources practices and principles applicable to the work.Working knowledge of day-to-day financial processes and the ability to oversee, track and ensure accuracy of payroll records, accounts payable, accounts receivable, credit card transactions, etc.Working knowledge of the organization, policies, and operations of a library or similar organization. Working knowledge or lived experience of the principles of reconciliation, decolonization, anti-racism, equity, accessibility and inclusion.Intermediate to advanced MS Office skills, particularly Word and Excel.Basic project management skills.Strong business ethics.Demonstrated commitment to continuing education in human resources or related fields.4. Desirable Training and ExperienceCompletion of a post-secondary program or degree in business or public administration, human resources or a related field, plus 3 to 5 years related experience in an office setting (including human resources) – or an equivalent combination of education and experience. Experience in a unionized, government or non-profit environment, and experience with organizational development activities such as training, DEI initiatives and staff engagement, is highly desirable.5. Required Licences, Certificates and RegistrationsNone. Compensation $33.25 - $39.14 (pay grade 18; 2024 rates - under review) + benefits Closes: 15 September, 2024 North Vancouver City Library North Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
